let's break down the formula
alphabet[26 * is_lower_char + (ord(letter) - ord('A') - 6 * is_lower_char + 13) % 26]
26 * is_lower_char -> if lower case we need to add 26 since we have the order AB...ab...
ord(letter) - ord('A') -> find the index gives us a number from:
0 -> 25 (CAPITAL LETTERS)
26 -> 31 (SPECIAL CHARACTERS [, \, ], ^, _, `)
32 -> 57 (LOWERCASE LETTERS)
-6 * is_lower_char -> if a lowercase we need to subtract the special characters from our index
+ 13 -> conversion to rot
(formula) % 26 -> gives us a number 0 -> 25 (inclusive) the index of our letter in the alphabet
